    Request executor provided by FirmwaresApi. Use this class if you want to schedule firmware update through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   kontaktCloud.firmwares().scheduleUpdate()
      .forDevices("4DgT", "8JkU")
      .withVersion("4.0")
      .execute();
    Keep in mind that devices and version must be specified so invocations of forDevices and withVersion methods are mandatory. Otherwise an exception will be thrown.
